post.description:
Search contacts by custom attributes.

Filter format:
- Simple: {"attribute_key": "value"}
- Range: {"attribute_key": {"gte": 100, "lte": 1000}}
- Contains: {"attribute_key": {"contains": "value"}}
- In list: {"attribute_key": {"in": ["val1", "val2"]}}
- Exists: {"attribute_key": {"exists": true}}

Executes a function call from OpenAI Realtime API.

The Realtime API sends function calls here when the agent decides
to use a tool. We map the function name to a PydanticAI tool,
execute it, and return the result.

Request body:
{
    "name": "get_nps_trend",
    "arguments": {"period": "week", "limit": 12},
    "call_id": "call_abc123",
    "org_id": 4145,
    "user_id": 123
}

Response:
{
    "call_id": "call_abc123",
    "output": {
        "trend_data": [...],
        "summary": "NPS increased by 5 points"
    }
}

Adapter endpoint for ZenGuide widget.

This endpoint translates between zenguide.js format and zagents format,
allowing the widget to use the existing zagents backend without duplication.

Request format (from zenguide.js):
{
    "message": "How do I create a survey?",
    "context": {
        "currentRoute": "/dashboard",
        "userRole": "admin",
        "conversationHistory": [...]
    }
}

Response format (expected by zenguide.js):
{
    "reply": "To create a survey...",
    "actions": [
        {"type": "navigate", "route": "/zen-surveys/create"},
        {"type": "highlight", "selector": ".create-survey-btn"}
    ]
}
